abstract: Investors were trying to assess how much confidence to place in the European banking sector after a review of banks deemed the bulk of them healthy.
snippet: Investors were trying to assess how much confidence to place in the European banking sector after a review of banks deemed the bulk of them healthy.
lead_paragraph: Shares of Italian banks led European stocks lower on Monday, as investors sought to assess a review of European banks that deemed most of them healthy and a survey showed confidence in German business falling.

headline.main: European Stocks Decline After Most Banks Pass E.C.B. Stress Tests
